wikipedia_page.main: Frederick George Banbury, 1st Baron Banbury of Southam  (2 December 1850 – 13 August 1936), known as Sir Frederick Banbury, 1st Baronet, from 1903 to 1924, was a British businessman and Conservative Member of Parliament.
